Description: Fragment of neck and handle of a pottery transport amphora. Clay near coarse, micaceous, red-brown. Oval stamp. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 201, 52? A parallel in the Benaki collection, Alexandria Museum, is from the same die.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1542)
